# ── WHITELIST MODE: ignore EVERYTHING, then re-allow code & docs only. ──
# The folder holds live financial data (MIS exports, per-vertical reports,
# persistent stores) and credentials — none of that may ever reach GitHub.
*

# code
!.gitignore
!*.py
!requirements.txt

# docs (text only — PDFs/DOCX/screenshots may embed real figures)
!README.md
!CLAUDE.md
!MAINTAINER_GUIDE.md
!USER_SOP.md
!AUTOMATION_REPORT.md
!WALKTHROUGH.md

# app config (example only — NEVER the real secrets.toml)
!.streamlit/
.streamlit/*
!.streamlit/secrets.toml.example
!.streamlit/config.toml

# assets
!Recykal logo.jpg

# explicit re-blocks (belt & braces even in whitelist mode)
secrets.toml
databases/
__pycache__/
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.pdf
*.docx
*.pptx
*.parquet
*.pkl
walkthrough_shots/
model_artifacts_national/
MIS Docs*/
_build_doc.py
detector.py
*.txt
!requirements.txt
desktop.ini
~$*

# ── baseline data for the hosted app ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Company-approved (06-07-2026): the private repo doubles as the data baseline
# for Streamlit Cloud (its disk resets on redeploy). Persistent stores + the
# manual per-vertical report files (freeze source) ship with the app.
# Monthly maintenance: drop the new "till DD-MM" files here, commit, push.
!persistent/
persistent/*
!persistent/*.parquet
!persistent/*.pkl
!Profitability Report of *.xlsx
